1
00:00:05,331 --> 00:00:08,855
Guru Mahārāj says,
“It’s interesting that the word ‘ṛṣīs’ is used.”

2
00:00:09,385 --> 00:00:11,820
[Reality Observers]

3
00:00:12,251 --> 00:00:18,368
In the Sanskrit, it means dṛśi, dṛṣṭvā,
‘to see, observe.’

4
00:00:18,368 --> 00:00:22,316
He said,
“They’re observers of reality.”

5
00:00:22,316 --> 00:00:26,517
‘Seers’ in that sense.
Darśan means ‘to see’.

6
00:00:26,517 --> 00:00:31,883
It’s synonymous with philosophy
and viewpoint—perspective.

7
00:00:31,904 --> 00:00:40,737
The Sanskrit word for ‘to create’ is
sārṣṭi or sṛṣṭi.

8
00:00:41,491 --> 00:00:46,612
The ṛṣīs, 
they’re not creating anything.

9
00:00:46,612 --> 00:00:57,558
And even—just as a side point—
great literary analysts

10
00:00:57,558 --> 00:01:03,165
will actually point out that all writers,
in varying degrees,

11
00:01:03,165 --> 00:01:06,335
are under the influence
of other writers.

12
00:01:06,335 --> 00:01:10,367
No one’s writing anything “original”.

13
00:01:10,367 --> 00:01:13,968
Someone even wrote a book called
The Anatomy of Influence.

14
00:01:13,968 --> 00:01:16,696
You can find how someone is influenced

15
00:01:16,696 --> 00:01:18,624
by another thinker, another thinker,
another thinker …

16
00:01:18,624 --> 00:01:22,338
It’s like a Guru-paramparā.

17
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:26,143
You can make
an original expression,

18
00:01:26,143 --> 00:01:29,933
but to say that you’re
just totally creating something

19
00:01:29,933 --> 00:01:34,385
without any influence from anyone,
is a dishonest position.

20
00:01:34,396 --> 00:01:42,261
So the ṛṣīs
—jñāninas tattva-darśinaḥ (Bg: 4.34)—

21
00:01:42,261 --> 00:01:46,100
what they’ve observed,
what’s been revealed to them,

22
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:49,060
they’re expressing;
they’re giving vent to that.

23
00:01:49,291 --> 00:01:52,264
All these things
are connected thematically.

24
00:01:52,264 --> 00:01:55,765
We shouldn’t think,
“Oh, the Upaniṣads say one thing,

25
00:01:55,765 --> 00:01:57,990
and then there’s the Purāṇas,
they say another,

26
00:01:57,990 --> 00:01:59,941
and then there’s another one
that says this,

27
00:01:59,941 --> 00:02:02,030
and there’s another book
that says that …”

28
00:02:02,030 --> 00:02:04,111
If you think like that,

29
00:02:04,111 --> 00:02:07,786
it means you don’t understand
the unified field theory

30
00:02:07,786 --> 00:02:14,587
of Kṛṣṇa conception, Gauḍīya Darśan,
Mahāprabhu, and Guru Mahārāj.

31
00:02:14,587 --> 00:02:16,565
It’s all connected.

